Visual Suggestions

  • This section will be in two parts - Text & Pictures
  • Now that you know the data, based on your insight, what are some of changes you would suggest to stop some of the problems you see.  1st identify a problem  in the data and then come up with a solution to that problem.
  • In the text portion, you will give 2-3 problems  solutions. 
  • Each step should be numbered
  • In the Pictures section you will find a picture that represents each solution.
  • In the pictures, you could take screenshots of actual parts of your project or you could show pictures that relate to your problem.  Remember to always capture the hearts of the audience.
  • Numbers must be numbered with same font / size / text / color to keep consistency
  • There should be no titles except before the numbered steps


Examples:


 Suggestions

  1. There are a range of shark attack prevention techniques employed to reduce the risk of shark attack and keep people safe. They include removing sharks by various fishing methods, separating people and sharks, as well as observation, education and various technology-based solutions. However, many of these technologies are still in development.
  2. Don’t enter the water in areas of known shark activity. Known hot spots in southern California include San Onofre, Seal Beach and Sunset beaches. Swimming in groups and avoiding large schools of bait fish also helps to prevent Shark attacks.
  3. Pay attention to Nature’s signs. Circling birds, splashing water, a dead whale, feeding seals and dolphins may also indicate a shark is near. Sharks are most active from sunset to sunrise, so avoid being in the water between those times.
